In our group project we are trying to minize our total costs to produce the highest profit. To do this we selected a busy time 5 - 7:30 in the restaurant. We had costs of each employee during those hours, as well as a waiting costs related to how many servers we had on the floor. We ran a simulation tracking profit on having different number of servers on the floor. The results showed that 11 servers resulted in the highest profit.

We learned that there a multiple amount of things need to be considered in trying to solve a problem like this. We had to use a predicted number of sales to determine what our demand distribution could be. In additon we need to know many different costs to get a result that would be most realistice.
